{"word":"προσακτέος","slug":"προσακτέος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>προσακτέος</b></el> <el>(προσακτέος, ον,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:verbal Adjective'>verb. <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a></a> of <a href='S:προσάγω'><el>προσάγω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>one must bring to</i> or <i>near</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>one must introduce</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristotle'>Arist.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}